        {
            "text": "The best photos appear to come alive because they contain peak action. This lesson will teach you to capture photos with peak action.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "header": "Next", 
            "text": "Start", 
            "type": "ButtonCard", 
            "id": "milestone_start", 
            "icon": "down"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A photograph must illustrate a story or scene in a single moment. To do that it has to be the right moment. This is called the moment of peak action.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_1", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "2.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "The pitcher is captured in mid-throw, the moment of peak action.", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "2.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Good photographs are about action and emotion. The most powerful images capture the moment at a scene when action and emotions are at their most visually expressive.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_2", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "1.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "Peak action is shown here at the moment the batter strikes the ball.", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "1.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Look for the moment of peak action when a behavior completes. This moment is often the height of peak action.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_3", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "4.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "Peak action is shown here at the moment the player reacts.", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "4.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The moment of peak action can be a powerful reaction. Don't focus only on primary characters, look to bystanders or the audience for great visual moments.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_4", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "5.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "Peak action is shown here at the moment the players interact.", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "5.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Don't photograph the first moment. Observe the scene, look for action, then wait for the right time to capture your moment.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_5", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "6.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "Peak action is here in the the player's frustration.", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "6.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is important to remember that sometimes a moment of peak action is more subtle, even intimate.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_6", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Anticipation and position are key to capturing peak action. Do not chase the action. Set up and wait to capture the best moment to tell your story.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_7", 
            "references": [
                "capture_peak_action::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
